RT @DrLeanaWen: Great Q @Yamiche: Why has the CDC stopped monitoring breakthrough infections, except in severe #covid19? 

Answer from @CDC…

Epis weigh in on how vaccinations change what they are comfortable doing. "More than at any time in the last year, most are feeling hopeful that Covid-19 will eventually become just another risk in daily life, but not one that paralyzes us."

https://t.co/D2DfXOZ9KR

RT @HelenBranswell: And yes, kids 12-15 will soon be able to get vaccinated with the #Pfizer #Covid19 vaccine.
https://t.co/qrxqv5Hdpz
RT @drdagly: Last night before I intubated a lovely man with COVID, he insisted on calling his boss to explain why he wouldn’t be into work…

"But we have to name a problem in order to solve it. Covering COVID-19 is trauma reporting."

I reached this line and started tearing up. It's been a hard year. 

Thank you @OliviaMesser for taking the time to name the problem. & a big hug to all my fellow COVID reporters. https://t.co/myaCCbchoz
